snippet.textDisplay: You cant clear the codes because 2018 and up Chryslers require a 12+8 harness.  There's basically a security module called an sgm that blocks you from clearing codes.  You can buy the harness online.  It plugs into the module to bypass it.  Module is usually behind the radio in the dash.  https://www.amazon.com/Bosting-Adaptor-Chrysler-Programming-Connector/dp/B07S91VZXT

Fault codes usually self clear after a 3 or 4 "start cycle". Every time you turn the ignition on the O.B.D. computer "checks" all systems onboard it will take a reading every "key" turn if no fault is found after so many times the computer will clear itself and switch the warning light(s) off.
Brill vid boys, keep fixing them motors👍
